<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-1978] Ruby: Thrift should allow for the SSL verify mode to be set</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-1978</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Ruby SSL verify mode cannot be specified, which means thrift cannot be used against servers with self-signed certificates over SSL. The suggested fix is to expose the SSL verification mode as a constructor argument in lib/rb/lib/thrift/transport/http_client_transport.rb.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
